(13 Nov. 2004)

Integrared gettext-support for I18n compliant
multi language support.

when gettext is not available, the english version
is shown at runtime.

see:
http://www.php.net/manual/en/ref.gettext.php
http://www.onlamp.com/pub/a/php/2002/06/13/php.html?page=1

in inc/header.inc.php i added a constant specifying
the language (locale) to be used. I also added a
new file inc/gettext.inc.php that is included here.

All constant Strings in the php scripts are now
converted with the gettext function.

In HTML-Mode this is done by adding:
<?= gettext("myString")?>
where myString should be put out.

In PHP-parts of the script, just use
gettext("myString") instead of "myString"

After changing php-files:

The batch file gettext_generate.bat will
generate a new english version of the resource
file message.po in the directory 
locale/en/LC_MESSAGES

It also merges the changes with the existing
german translation in locale/en/LC_MESSAGES

After that, the translation can be done in the
language specific message.po

After translation, gettext_compile.bat must be
called to generate a binary version of the 
resoruce file that will later be used.
Only these files (messages.mo) are needed at runtime.

To add more languages, just create more directories
and copy/paste new lines in the two batch files 
to automatically include them in the merge / compile
process.

please change the pathes to the gettext-binaries
in the batch files before calling them.

gettext is available on many platforms. you have to
adopt the batch files to shell scripts to use them
under *nix or linux. this should be very easy since
the batch files are really simple.